refilling underground tanks at the Thrifty Oil Co. gas station at Topanga 
Canyon Boulevard and Bassett Street in Canoga Park about noon Thursday. The 
fire was extinguished in about 15 minutes but closed a portion of Topanga 
Canyon Boulevard for about an hour. No one was hurt. Fire Department officials 
blamed the fire on gasoline that overflowed in one of the underground tanks and 
formed a pool along a Bassett Street curb. The gasoline was ignited when a 
driver parked her car there and turned off the engine. That car and two others 
were destroyed. STEWART HALUSKI / For The Times 
