<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROHRABACHER'S OIL STANCE CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With chagrin I read about Rep. Dana Rohrabacher's (R-Lomita) current 
pro-offshore oil-drilling stand. This lack of concern for the environment, this 
utter disregard for his constituents' wishes, this unconscionable about-face, 
(his office was contacted before his election and we were assured of his 
anti-drilling stance) exhibit extremely poor judgment and disqualify him as our 
representative in Congress. 
</P>
<P>
Mr. Rohrabacher has been ill-advised. Voters are independent thinkers and 
cannot be led by the nose, regardless of party affiliation. The matter of 
offshore oil-drilling is of vital importance to us. Unless Rep. Rohrabacher 
clearly restates his position, it is with great regret that, for the first time 
in decades, my family and many fellow concerned Republicans will have to vote 
for a Democrat. 
</P>
<P>
STELLA LaROSE 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Palos Verdes 
</P>
