<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA REINA ROUTS BISHOP DIEGO BEHIND PERFECT GAME, 37-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Reina High crushed Bishop Diego, 37-0, Thursday in a Tri-Valley League 
softball game at Bishop Diego that was shortened to five innings because of a 
10-run rule. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman right-hander Michelle St. Pierre pitched a perfect game and the 
Regents (7-3, 2-0 in league play), who scored 15 runs in the third inning, 
collected 18 hits and capitalized on 22 walks and 11 errors by Bishop Diego 
(3-3, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
Last season, La Reina hammered Bishop Diego, 41-1, in a game featuring a 23-run 
inning. 
</P>
<P>
"I feel good about the pitching and defense, but the rest of it. . . . It 
doesn't do you any good," La Reina Coach Don Hyatt said. "How do you say, 
'Congratulations, you played a nice game' ?" 
</P>
<P>
St. Pierre (3-2) was four for five with five runs batted in and five runs 
scored. Carolyn Russo was four for six with five RBIs and four runs scored. 
Sheri Sisco hit a three-run home run in the third inning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
