<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sega Wins Joe Montana Endorsement: Video game maker Sega of America signed 
quarterback Joe Montana -- a self-proclaimed "video nut" -- to his largest 
endorsement deal yet, outbidding industry giant Nintendo with a 
multimillion-dollar offer. The five-year contract gives Sega the exclusive 
rights to make and sell home video games, arcade games and computer software 
using the Super Bowl champion's likeness. 
</P>
<P>
The exact size of the contract was not disclosed, but Montana said it was 
bigger than any other deal he has signed to date, including his contract with 
shoemakers L.A. Gear, which was estimated at $3 million to $5 million, although 
Montana said those estimates were high. Montana will help Sega, based in South 
San Francisco, develop football video games in which he will star. 
</P>
</TEXT>
