<P>
BRITISH BOXER REMAINS CRITICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAMBRIDGE, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A British boxer remained in critical condition today after undergoing brain 
surgery after his victory in a regional title bout. 
</P>
<P>
Doctors said Mark Goult, a 20-year-old bantamweight, was fighting for his life 
at Addenbrooke's Hospital in Cambridge. 
</P>
<P>
Goult complained of severe headaches shortly after defeating Danny Porter for 
the British southern area bantamweight title Tuesday night in Norwich. 
</P>
<P>
He underwent a five-hour operation that night to remove a blood clot from his 
brain. 
